excerpt: Iconic landmark for Floridian-Caribbean cuisine & key lime pie, with a funky setting.
detail_description: Blue Heaven is a renowned dining spot in Key West, known for its iconic Floridian-Caribbean cuisine and delectable key lime pie. address: 729 Thomas St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Traditional Cuban home cooking & housemade sangria in a casual, family-friendly setting.
detail_description: El Siboney Restaurant is a casual, family-friendly spot known for its traditional Cuban home cooking and housemade sangria. address: 900 Catherine St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Cozy, high-end hotel eatery celebrated for its genteel ambiance & inventive New American cooking.
detail_description: Cafe Marquesa is a charming and upscale restaurant located just off Duval Street in Key West's historic district. Despite its central location, the restaurant offers a serene atmosphere with a lush garden providing privacy from the bustling tourist area. The starters, including shrimp and grits with andouille sausage and country ham, are highly recommended.

address: 600 Fleming St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Offbeat eatery in a driftwood shack doling out fried fish, conch fritters, hot dogs & sandwiches.
detail_description: B.O.'s Fish Wagon is a quirky seafood shack located in Key West, known for its laid-back atmosphere and delicious food. The eatery gained recognition from the NY Times and even caught the attention of Bobby Flay. The menu offers a variety of seafood dishes with a local twist, perfect for grabbing on-the-go or enjoying at the open-air eatery adorned with eclectic decor.

The menu features a variety of sandwiches including crab cake and shrimp salad, as well as fried fish and grilled lobster tail. Additionally, the market provides fresh fish to go for those who prefer cooking at home.

address: 801 Eaton St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Charming seaside eatery with open-air patios serving up a menu of Latin American-style small plates.

Guests can also indulge in the must-try dessert - Key Lime Pie.

address: 245 Front St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Tiny, husband-&-wife-run food stand serving eclectic, inventive takes on tacos, burritos & burgers.

excerpt: Seafood-focused American eatery set in an 1884 house with wraparound balconies for people-watching.

address: 7305, 207 Petronia St #101, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Conch & Caribbean-style eats star at this laid-back eatery overlooking the seaport & marina.

The restaurant's location pays homage to Key West's conch industry history, with the area once being known for its abundance of queen conchs.

excerpt: Funky open-air restaurant right off the sand featuring fish-focused Italian fare & ocean views.

address: 1000 Atlantic Blvd, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Breezy Italian eatery offering a shaded garden patio, wood-fired pizzas & an old-world wine list.

name: Onlywood Pizzeria Trattoria
address: 613-1/2 Duval St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Casual shop serving creative donuts & coffee in a relaxed space with robot decor.

address: 420 Eaton St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Chill spot adorned with local art serving globally inspired veggie & seafood eats, plus beer & wine.

The cafe boasts vibrant decor and offers both indoor and outdoor seating options. Whether you're craving traditional French crepes or a simple bacon, egg, and cheese sandwich, Banana Cafe has something to satisfy every palate. Vegetarians will find several appealing options on the menu as well.

address: 1215 Duval St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Long-standing mostly outdoor cafe with an old-school American menu plus lively karaoke.

The menu also surprises with unique offerings such as crab cake Benedict infused with Caribbean flavors and indulgent Key lime-stuffed French toast adorned with strawberries.

excerpt: Relaxed dockside seafood eatery at the Ocean Key Resort & Spa with water views, drinks & live music.

The pier is known for serving Key West seafood classics like conch fritters and crab cakes, as well as Cuban cuisine.
name: Sunset Pier
address: 0 Duval St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: American fare & house brews in a chill, aviation-themed space with a courtyard shaded by palm trees.

The outdoor patio exudes island charm, offering a perfect setting to savor their popular street corn and avocado bowl.

excerpt: Dessert bar offering an extensive menu of decadent treats in a dimly lit, intimate space.

excerpt: American cafe serving po' boys, conch fritters & the like in a circa-1838 house with outdoor seats.

The cafe offers a diverse menu featuring traditional American fare like sandwiches, as well as specialty dishes such as jerk chicken and jambalaya. Visitors can enjoy outdoor seating while indulging in delicious meals like the Chicken Broccolini, Jerk Chicken, and Shrimp Po'Boy.

address: 310 Duval St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Eatery serving homemade pastas & other Italian classics in quarters with island-inspired decor.

Located just off Duval Street, it provides indoor seating as well as an open-air counter for prime people-watching.

address: 425 Greene St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Mediterranean spot serving breakfast, lunch & dinner in a tranquil indoor space or outdoor terrace.

The menu includes twists on the classic Benedict, Italian-inspired breakfast carbonara, and a selection of unusual sandwiches, salads, and frittatas.

address: 425 Grinnell St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Airy corner spot with locally sourced seafood, salads & a raw bar, plus craft beers & wine.

The husband-wife duo behind the establishment has also opened another popular restaurant in the area. Inspired by oyster bars and sidewalk cafes in New York City's West Village, this spot is perfect for enjoying delicious meals and drink specials.

excerpt: Steak & seafood spot serves an artful New American menu & daily specials in a funky tropical space.

Despite its limited opening hours, it's a hidden gem recommended by locals and visitors alike. The intimate fine-dining setting exudes casual Key West style, offering fantastic food such as tuna and watermelon ceviche and fresh catch with banana salsa and lime butter sauce.

address: 424 Eaton St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Specialty French-style cafe preparing baked goods daily as well as cafe & more formal meals.
detail_description: La Grignote is a charming French-style cafe located in the elegant Upper Duval Street district. excerpt: Stylish old house with a big patio for globally accented American fare, plus a late-night wine bar.

The ambiance is enhanced by twinkling lights and soothing jazz music, creating a relaxed yet elegant setting. As you explore the menu, you'll find an array of tantalizing small plates perfect for sharing or enjoying solo.

excerpt: Rustic joint with laid-back vibes dishing up signature breakfasts plus surf 'n' turf since 1909.

name: Little Pearl

The saloon is famous for its strong drinks and decent food options like conch fritters and fish nuggets.
name: Hog's Breath Saloon
address: 400 Front St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: A big outdoor patio overlooking a bustling street attracts crowds to this fish-focused eatery & bar.
detail_description: Mangoes Restaurant is a popular fish-focused eatery and bar in Key West, offering a vibrant outdoor patio with views of the bustling street. With over 40 years of history, it brings Caribbean flair to its menu, featuring dishes inspired by Bahamian, Cuban, and West Indies culture. The restaurant has recently undergone renovations under new ownership, emphasizing local flavors and produce. From blackened cobia to jerk-style chicken and spicy sweet potatoes, the menu offers a variety of flavorful options.

address: 700 Duval St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

The bar encourages audience participation, creating a fun and engaging atmosphere where guests can even become part of the show.

name: Southernmost Beach Caf√©
address: 1405 Duval St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

detail_description: 5 Brothers Grocery and Sandwich Shop is a long-standing corner market in Key West, known for its authentic Cuban coffee, hand-rolled cigars, and delicious sandwiches. The restaurant's vintage charm is complemented by breathtaking harbor vistas, creating an inviting atmosphere for savoring their delectable grilled meats.

excerpt: Chill takeaway window with a beach-shack vibe for breakfast/lunch sandwiches with local seafood.

The small market offers daily essentials, unique products, organic produce and groceries for cooking at home, healthy treats, supplements or organic beauty products.

address: 615 Duval St, Key West, FL 33040, USA

excerpt: Sushi, sashimi & cooked Japanese dishes, plus sake & wine, served in a chic lounge environment.
